225 during the postpartalpostpartum period until the conditions of
226 the client and newborn are stabilized.
227 (h) A licensed midwife shall instruct the client
228 regarding the requirements of the administration of eye
229 ointment ordered by the Alabama Department of Public Health
230 pursuant to Section 22-20-2.
231 (i) A licensed midwife shall instruct the client
232 regarding the requirements of administration of newborn health
233 screening ordered by the Alabama Department of Public Health
234 pursuant to Section 22-20-3.
235 (j) A licensed midwife shall file a birth certificate
236 for each birth in accordance with the requirements of Section
237 22-9A-7.
238 (k) A licensed midwife shall collect clinical data
239 under the Midwives Alliance of North America Statistics
